%C A099095 Row sums are A007482. Diagonal sums are A053088. The Riordan array (1,s+tx) defines T(n,k)=binomial(k,n-k)s^k(t/s)^(n-k). The row sums satisfy a(n)=s*a(n-1)+t*a(n-2) and the diagonal sums satisfy a(n)=s*a(n-2)+t*a(n-3).
